<title>SOUTH KOREA: Seoul to allow forex-denominated securities issues.</title>
<headline>Seoul to allow forex-denominated securities issues.</headline>
<dateline>SEOUL 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Korea will allow domestic issues of foreign exchange-denominated securities by foreigners and local listed companies from May 1, the Ministry of Finance and Economy said on Thursday.</p>
<p>Foreigners eligible for issues of such securities include international organisations, foreign governments, financial institutions and companies.</p>
<p>To be eligible, foreigners as well as local listed firms must also have BBB or higher-grade credit ratings.</p>
<p>Procedures for foreign issuers will be similar to those applied to won-denominated securities issues by foreigners.</p>
</text>
